        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 12:48PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 1248 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles west of Smoky Mountains-Twentymile Creek, or 14 miles east of
Madisonville, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Citico Beach, Tariffville, Talassee, Happy Valley, McGee Carson
Peninsula, and Deals Gap.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
